############################################################################
# HOPR INSTALLATION PROCEDURE
############################################################################

#############################  PREREQUISITES  ##############################
          
HOPR supports Linux-based systems only requires a x86_64 compliant platform.
It has been tested on the following platforms:
Ubuntu 12.04 and newer including derivates
SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 11 SP3 and newer

Compilers:
HOPR requires a C and a Fortran 2003 compliant compiler, e.g. provided by
GNU Compiler Collection 4.6+, Intel C/Fortran Compiler 12+ (recommended)

The following libraries are required, if not mentioned otherwise including
their development headers:
libc6, zlib, BLAS/LAPACK (or compatible, e.g. ATLAS, MKL)

#############################  COMPILING  ##################################

To compile HOPR, specify the compiler in the file Makefile.defs,
either Intel
COMPILER=INTEL
or GNU:
COMPILER=GNU

then compile the code with

> make

this will also compile all libraries in the share folder.

To compile HOPR with MPI support (e.g. to link other libraries using MPI)
or with debug flags add the Flag _MPI or _DEBUG to the COMPILER string,
e.g. COMPILER=GNU_MPI_DEBUG
Other options are descibed in the Makefile.defs Header.

In case you want to use a precompiled HDF5 version on your system set the
option BUILD_HDF5=<empty>, then the path to HDF5 can be specified by
the environment variable $HDF5_DIR .
